thermal pressure is larger than the magnetic field pressure downstream.

From Figure~\ref{fig:etarelic} we come to the extreme requirement that more than several percent of the kinetic energy
flux crossing the shock should be converted into acceleration of relativistic electrons \citep[e.g.,][]{2012ApJ...756...97K}. This argues against standard DSA and provides support for re-acceleration for which this requirement does not apply. 






